column5: Is the highway 105 open to normal traffic, yet?Headed that way Saturday and hoping to not have to use a detour.Thanks,Pooch

I had friends that came home last Saturday. They said they drove thru a small amount of water in one area, but the road was not closed. Not sure if things have gotten worse since then, but I would doubt it.

We also came through last Saturday. There was one place with water on the road that was about 10" deep. The rivers up there were all blown. Hopefully they'll get a little dry weather and the problems will end. Good luck!

Drove through it last Friday night. There are highway workers with big time lights before the detour. Talked to the guy. He said there was about a foot of water. We had your standard truck and boat. Said to stay in the middle and we would be fine. He spoke the truth. No way a car could get through though. If they have had rain this week, it is probably still flooded.

Same experience last Friday with two trucks pulling boats and got thru with no problem...coming home yesterday the road was clear but with all the water on the sides a good rain could flood it again..same with 17 going East out of VB...
